****************Giving Permissions to Users*********************

Add files for the project then we will give permissions to the file.

Three categories of Linux permissions to file:
(drw- r-x  r--)
 |     |    |
User  Group Others
Permission Permission Permission

Number for Alloting Permission

r – Read → 4
w – Write → 2
x – Execute → 1

For full permission:
4 + 2 + 1 = 7

              --->>Flow chart<----
Create user
↓
Assign permissions (requirement)

Command:chmod (number) filename
Example: chmod 611 file1 (for user)

For other users: 
chmod 647 test2
Change the number according to requirement.

To change the ownership:
Command: chown user filename
Example: chown hyderabad test1
         (Command → user → filename)

To change the group:
Command:chgrp groupname filename
Example:chgrp hyderabad test2
        (Command → groupname → filename)




